 ## Unreleased
 
+- Added depth-2 motif-lifecycle report helpers (frac-0025): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/motif_lifecycle.py` now exposes frozen `MotifLifecycleStep` and `MotifLifecycleReport` dataclasses plus pure helpers `lifecycle_state_index`, `build_lifecycle_step`, `canonical_lifecycle_path`, `build_lifecycle_report`, and `summarize_lifecycle_report` so composer/diagnostics callers can advance a motif through the one canonical lifecycle path and emit a JSON-safe operator summary with ordered history, current/terminal state, valid next states, canonical state counts, contour/rhythm/material deltas, and per-step state-band/material diagnostics. Existing transition rules, deterministic transformations, `advance(...)`, `MotifLifecycleManager`, and repertoire-shape recall behavior are preserved; `tests/test_motif_lifecycle_depth.py` pins the new report surface, manager end-to-end agreement, JSON-safe summaries, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_motif_lifecycle.py` and the startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
+
 - Added depth-2 score-tree report helpers (frac-0024): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/score_tree.py` now exposes frozen `ScoreTreeSectionReport` and `ScoreTreeReport` dataclasses plus pure helpers `motif_lifecycle_band`, `section_phrase_load_band`, `count_motif_lifecycle_states`, `build_score_tree_section_report`, `build_score_tree_report`, and `summarize_score_tree_report` so composer/diagnostics callers can resolve a `ScoreTree` into operator-readable shape diagnostics — per-section view (id, scene, function, harmonic role/function, cadence, groove, transition intent, transform strength, target duration, phrase count, named phrase-load band, ordered de-duplicated motif refs across the section's phrases, and a `production_course_complete` flag against `PRODUCTION_COURSE_KEYS`) and tree-level view (piece id, title, form family/class/composition mode, ending family, planned duration, section/motif/phrase counts, ordered `motif_lifecycle_counts` covering every `MOTIF_LIFECYCLE_STATES` entry with zeros for absent states, ordered tuple of unreferenced motif ids, and per-section reports) — and emit a JSON-safe summary mirroring those fields. Existing `MOTIF_LIFECYCLE_STATES`, `PRODUCTION_COURSE_KEYS`, `MotifNode`, `PhraseNode`, `SectionNode`, and `ScoreTree.to_dict` / `to_json` / `from_dict` / `minimal` semantics are preserved so the JSON round-trip and minimal-tree behavior continue unchanged; `tests/test_score_tree_depth.py` pins lifecycle-band mapping (with `"unclassified"` fallback for unknown states), phrase-load band cutpoints, canonical-only lifecycle counting, populated-tree section/tree shape, JSON round-trip stability, minimal-tree zero-state handling, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_score_tree.py` and `tests/test_smoke_narrative_script.py` remain regression anchors (the latter for the narrative HTTP `/healthz` + `/readyz` + bearer-token hardening surface).
 
 - Added depth-2 sampler-dispatch planning helpers (frac-0023): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/sampler_dispatch.py` now exposes a frozen `SamplerDispatchPlan` plus `grain_density_band`, `sampler_synth_arg_pairs`, `build_s_new_args`, `build_sampler_dispatch_plan`, and `summarize_sampler_dispatch_plan` so diagnostics and composer callers can inspect a concrete `sw_sampler` dispatch before or after buffer loading. The plan reports sample path, mode, key, buffer state, density band, key-derived or explicit transposition, gain-db-adjusted effective amp, FX preset pairs, and the canonical `/s_new` synth argument pairs; live `SamplerDispatcher.dispatch_sample` now uses the same `build_s_new_args` helper, preserving existing OSC ordering and lifecycle behavior. `tests/test_sampler_dispatch_depth.py` pins named density bands, loaded/unloaded plan output, JSON-safe summaries, end-to-end plan-to-dispatch matching, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_sampler_dispatch.py` and the startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
